                  "pkg:deb/debian/passwd@1%3A4.19.3-2?arch=amd64\u0026distro=debian\u0026upstream=shadow"
                ],
                "security-severity": "3.6"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2017-17740-libldap2",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2017-17740 low vulnerability for libldap2 package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "contrib/slapd-modules/nops/nops.c in OpenLDAP through 2.4.45, when both the nops module and the memberof overlay are enabled, attempts to free a buffer that was allocated on the stack, which allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (slapd crash) via a member MODDN operation."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2017-17740",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2017-17740\nSeverity: low\nPackage: libldap2\nVersion: 2.6.10+dfsg-1+b1\nFix Version: \nType: deb\nLocation: /var/lib/dpkg/status\nData Namespace: debian:distro:debian:unstable\nLink: [CVE-2017-17740](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2017-17740)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2017-17740**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| low  | libldap2  | 2.6.10+dfsg-1+b1  |   | deb  | /var/lib/dpkg/status  | debian:distro:debian:unstable  | [CVE-2017-17740](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2017-17740)  |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:deb/debian/libldap2@2.6.10%2Bdfsg-1%2Bb1?arch=amd64\u0026distro=debian\u0026upstream=openldap%402.6.10%2Bdfsg-1"
                ],
                "security-severity": "7.5"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2011-3389-libgnutls30t64",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2011-3389 low vulnerability for libgnutls30t64 package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "The SSL protocol, as used in certain configurations in Microsoft Windows and Microsoft Internet Explorer, Mozilla Firefox, Google Chrome, Opera, and other products, encrypts data by using CBC mode with chained initialization vectors, which allows man-in-the-middle attackers to obtain plaintext HTTP headers via a blockwise chosen-boundary attack (BCBA) on an HTTPS session, in conjunction with JavaScript code that uses (1) the HTML5 WebSocket API, (2) the Java URLConnection API, or (3) the Silverlight WebClient API, aka a \"BEAST\" attack."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2011-3389",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2011-3389\nSeverity: low\nPackage: libgnutls30t64\nVersion: 3.8.12-3\nFix Version: \nType: deb\nLocation: /var/lib/dpkg/status\nData Namespace: debian:distro:debian:unstable\nLink: [CVE-2011-3389](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2011-3389)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2011-3389**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| low  | libgnutls30t64  | 3.8.12-3  |   | deb  | /var/lib/dpkg/status  | debian:distro:debian:unstable  | [CVE-2011-3389](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2011-3389)  |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:deb/debian/libgnutls30t64@3.8.12-3?arch=amd64\u0026distro=debian\u0026upstream=gnutls28"
                ],
                "security-severity": "4.3"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2005-2541-tar",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactDirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2005-2541 low vulnerability for tar package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Tar 1.15.1 does not properly warn the user when extracting setuid or setgid files, which may allow local users or remote attackers to gain privileges."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2005-2541",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2005-2541\nSeverity: low\nPackage: tar\nVersion: 1.35+dfsg-4\nFix Version: \nType: deb\nLocation: /var/lib/dpkg/status\nData Namespace: debian:distro:debian:unstable\nLink: [CVE-2005-2541](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2005-2541)",
